You define a sandbox of code using the `mod` keyword.

```rust
mod network {
    fn connect() {
        println!("Connected!");
    }
}
```
Modules act exactly like folders for your logic, grouping related functions together.

Instead of writing the whole module in `main.rs`, you simply declare it:

```rust
// In main.rs
mod network;
```
Then, Rust automatically looks for literally a file named `network.rs` identically in the exact same directory!
